title: For Sale:  454 Casull Ammo - 360 gr. L.B.T. - L.W.N. (1,425 fps/M.E. 1,623 ft. lbs.) - 20 Round Box (Big Game up to 2000 lbs.)
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=60

The .454 Casull is one cartridge that Buffalo Bore Ammunition does not load to it's full pressure limit. When loaded to it's full pressure potential the .454 Casull can become unreliable and unpleasant to shoot. At upper pressure levels, heavy bullets tend to jump crimp - tying up the cylinder. (wouldn't this be great in an emergency) Also, fired brass can stick in the chambers. 

Buffalo Bore Ammunition feels that a 360 gr. bullet (or 325 gr. bullet at 1525 fps) at 1425 fps is still very powerful, comfortable to shoot, and TOTALLY RELIABLE. At these levels, these bullets give up nothing in killing performance.

The HK USP Compact is a small frame pistol capable of firing the most powerful cartridges in 9 mm, .40 S&W, .45 ACP, and .357 SIG (by special order). Based on the full-size USP models, these handy pistols combine compact size with optimum effective shooting performance.

USP Compacts are smaller and lighter than large frame USPs. The reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases concealability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact semiautomatic pistols that use a difficult to shoot "two-finger grip" frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floorplates. To reduce the length of the slide and barrel on the USP Compact, the mechanical recoil reduction system found on large frame USPs has been replaced by a specially designed flat compression spring contained in the captive recoil spring assembly by a polymer absorber bushing. Snag one and when we talk, send me a picture of you and the new pamphlet, or you at the event and you will receive the special discount price. Remember this is for one day only! Check out the event, shoot the suppressor or NFA Firearms you want, and then get the Trust that allows to you get it! CarolinaGunTrust.com has been invited to this event, and we’re able to extend the invitation to everyone who wants to have some fun.The DPRC is a private club and we have to play by their rules. If you've joined  before, you may remember how things went…. but this time, things are a little different.

First, you have to pay to play. It’s $25 to get in. If you’re under 13 years old, the cost is $15. Tickets will be sold at the door and there will be food . These are DPRC’s rules, and the good news is that all proceeds go to a worthy cause – Friends of NRA. There will be drinks, hamburgers and chips available for a small fee to get you through the day.

Second, there will be several more vendors and manufacturers at the event this time. This means that there will be more toys for you to experience. The vendors and exhibitors include:

NC SILENCER

Templar Custom
Surefire
ACME Ammunition
Black Powder pistol and Rifle bay set up by club members
Special offerings by DPRC and Trace Armory
High power rifle (the club will have Garands on the rifle range at a cost of $5 per 8 round magazine)

Also there are various items being raffled including an Olympic Arms AR-15, Kimber Ultra Carry, Innovative Arms Grunt Suppressor, Thompson Machine Zephyr Suppressor, 1 Free NFA Gun Trust, plus some other surprises.  Did somebody say Machine Guns?...

If you have a suppressor or two or three pending ATF approval sitting in quarantine, come out and shoot some with NC SILENCER and the other Vendors. Please bring your own host gun(s) if you have them, and plenty of ammo. And of course, the Vendors will have several host guns and silencers that you’re welcome to try out.
